place.name: WICKENBY
place.gazetteerText: WICKENBY, a parish, with a r. station and two hamlets, in the district and county of Lincoln; on the Lincoln and Hull railway, 5¼ miles SSW of Market-Rasen. Post town, Wragby. Acres, 1,997. Real property, £2,983. Pop., 288. Houses, 56. The manor belongs to Mrs. Gillyatt. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £400.* Patron, the Rev.Nevile. The church is old. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
